<doc id="1179731" wikidata="Q5462780" url="?curid=1179731" title="Flummadiddle">
<text>Flummadiddle is a baked main course pudding consisting of stale bread, pork fat, molasses, and spices including cinnamon, allspice, and cloves. It was a part of early American cuisine, especially of New England fishermen.

