<doc id="1179754" wikidata="Q7055701" url="?curid=1179754" title="North Ings Farm Museum">
<text>The North Ings Farm Museum is a working farm museum containing a narrow gauge railway, running on a circuit of . It is located at Dorrington, between Lincoln and Sleaford, in Lincolnshire. The museum includes agricultural machinery and tractors, commercial vehicles, portable steam pumps and a fairground organ. The collection was opened to the public in 1990.

